# Architecture Rules — Menu Grading Tool

## Deployment Model
- **Runtime**: Vercel (frontend + API routes) or single VPS
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with App Router, TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- **Database**: PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM

## Tech Stack (Locked)
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend | Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui |
| Backend | Next.js API Routes |
| PDF Parsing | pdf.js for text extraction |
| OCR | Tesseract.js (client-fallback) + Google Vision API (preferred) |
| AI/LLM | Anthropic Claude API (primary), OpenAI GPT-4o (fallback) |
| Excel Parsing | xlsx (SheetJS) |
| Square API | Square Node.js SDK |
| Database | PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM |
| Auth | NextAuth.js with email provider |
| Charts | Recharts |
| Fuzzy Match | fuse.js |
| PDF Export | jspdf |

## NO-GO List
- ❌ Docker (Vercel handles deployment)
- ❌ Redis / Memcached
- ❌ Celery / RabbitMQ
- ❌ WebSockets (use polling or SSE for real-time)
- ❌ SQLAlchemy or any Python ORM (this is a Node.js project)
- ❌ CSS-in-JS libraries (use Tailwind)
- ❌ Other React frameworks (no Remix, no Gatsby)

## API Conventions
- All API routes under `/api/v1/`
- RESTful: GET (list/detail), POST (create), PUT (update), DELETE
- All responses: `{ data, meta }` or `{ error, detail }`
- Pagination: `?page=1&pageSize=20`

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/       # React components
│   ├── ui/          # shadcn/ui primitives
│   ├── upload/      # Upload flow components
│   ├── grading/     # Grading engine UI
│   ├── report/      # Report display components
│   ├── ai/          # Claude AI panel components
│   └── layout/      # Navigation, sidebar, header
├── lib/             # Core business logic
│   ├── grading/     # Rubric scoring engine
│   ├── parsers/     # PDF, image, Excel parsers
│   ├── square/      # Square API client
│   ├── ai/          # Claude AI integration
│   └── utils/       # Shared utilities
├── prisma/          # Database schema & migrations
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
├── stores/          # Zustand stores (if needed)
├── types/           # TypeScript type definitions
└── constants/       # Rubric weights, thresholds
```

## Code Quality
- One module = one responsibility
- Keep files under 300 lines
- Every module has a docstring/JSDoc explaining purpose
- All prices stored in cents (integers)
- All grading functions independently testable
- LLM calls must have graceful fallbacks
